JOHANNESBURG - Two suspects allegedly involved in the OR Tambo International Airport heist will appear at the Kempton Park magistrate's court on Friday. They are facing robbery charges after millions in foreign currency were stolen at the airport earlier this month.READ: OR Tambo heist: Police make major breakthroughSeven people have been arrested for the heist -- five of them appeared in court on Monday.Their case was postponed for a formal bail application on the 28 and 29 March.eNCA